{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/pyhf/pulls/1790", "id": 863092941, "node_id": "PR_kwDOBxSVwc4zccDN", "html_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/pyhf/pull/1790", "diff_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/pyhf/pull/1790.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/pyhf/pull/1790.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/pyhf/issues/1790", "number": 1790, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "feat: Use tbump over bump2version", "user": {"login": "matthewfeickert", "id": 5142394, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUxNDIzOTQ=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5142394?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert", "html_url": "https://github.com/matthewfeickert", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "# Description\r\n\r\n* Resolves #1756\r\n* Resolves #1223\r\n\r\nAdopt the use of `tbump` for bumping, tagging, and commiting version files in a controlled manner. The user of `tbump` allows for greater granularity and control on the version (e.g., can target release candidates like `v0.7.0rc1`) but also requires greater restraint on the developers (you can target any version). `tbump` also adds the ability to select regions of a matching file to target, so \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/scikit-hep/pyhf/blob/2533bd9b391e00614ad5e33781a4a0977f588263/src/pyhf/utils.py#L13\r\n\r\ncan be shielded from version bumps by accident (this addresses Issue #1223).\r\n\r\nFollowing PR #1632 and this PR we can migrate away from the [tag.yml workflow](https://github.com/scikit-hep/pyhf/blob/270d59d3900fdef7549015db45260e85f83e33b6/.github/workflows/tag.yml) and remove all `bump2verion` related files in another PR. This can also add in a CI/CD version bump system that will operate via `workflow_dispatch` that has safety checks in it (and also address Issue #725 as the system will be gone).\r\n\r\n# Checklist Before Requesting Reviewer\r\n\r\n- [x] Tests are passing\r\n- [x] \"WIP\" removed from the title of the pull request\r\n- [x] Selected an Assignee for the PR to be responsible for the log summary\r\n\r\n# Before Merging\r\n\r\nFor the PR Assignees:\r\n\r\n- [x] Summarize commit messages into a comprehensive review of the PR\r\n\r\n```\r\n* Add tbump to 'develop' extra and remove bump2version.\r\n* Add tbump.toml to configure tbump.\r\n   - Allow for valid versions to follow SemVer and also support release\r\ncandidates: <major>.<minor>.<patch>rc<candidate>\r\n   - Guard pyhf.utils.SCHEMA_VERSION against version bumps accidentally\r\nbumping the SCHEMA_VERSION.\r\n```", "created_at": "2022-02-25T04:51:31Z", "updated_at": "2022-03-02T04:15:17Z", "closed_at": "2022-03-02T04:15:16Z", "merged_at": "2022-03-02T04:15:15Z", "merge_commit_sha": "a8982e4aa8b9490ec7bc6d54f63ed55c0cfd8a95", "assignees": [{"login": "matthewfeickert", "id": 5142394, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUxNDIzOTQ=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5142394?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert", "html_url": "https://github.com/matthewfeickert", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/following{/other_user}", 